body:
I started Android Studio with the embedded inspector option disabled. Then I opened preferences and clicked the checkbox to enable it. I expected JxBrowser to be installed, but it wasn't. Shortly after that I notice an error had occurred. This is the stack trace.

I had also opened and closed this project a few times (during release testing) without restarting Android Studio. So it is quite possible that a stale disposable was hanging around from the first time the project was opened.
